From: bug-fix-campaign §6.4
Subject: Wrap user-facing chat completion in record_llm_call

The user-facing chat call (``POST /api/chat/completions`` →
``process_chat`` → ``chat_completion_handler``) is the single biggest
LLM cost in the system, but until this patch it was invisible to the
Prometheus surface — ``rag_tokens_prompt_total`` /
``rag_tokens_completion_total`` / ``rag_llm_ttft_seconds`` only saw
contextualizer / hyde / rewriter / SSE-stream traffic. Operators
couldn't answer "how much of today's vllm-chat budget went to actual
chat?" from dashboards.

This patch:
  1. Imports ``record_llm_call`` from ``ext.services.llm_telemetry`` at
     module load (try/except → no-op shim if ``ext`` isn't on path,
     so the upstream file remains usable in vanilla Open WebUI).
  2. Wraps the ``chat_completion_handler(...)`` call inside
     ``process_chat`` with the recorder context manager.
  3. Sets ``stage="user_chat"`` (distinct from the SSE path's
     ``stage="chat"`` so dashboards can break them out).
  4. Pulls ``kb`` from the chat metadata's ``kb_config`` JSONB
     (canonical post-migration-007 home for the user's KB selection)
     — comma-joined IDs become the ``kb`` label on
     ``rag_tokens_prompt_total``.
  5. Captures ``usage.prompt_tokens`` / ``usage.completion_tokens``
     from non-streaming JSON responses via ``response.body``. Streaming
     responses leave the counters at zero (recorder skips zero-valued
     increments); the TTFT histogram still fires from the recorder's
     ``finally`` timing block. Streaming token capture would require
     patching ``process_chat_response`` which has a much larger
     surface — out of scope here.

Re-apply this patch if upstream/ is re-vendored. Apply with::

    git apply patches/0007_chat_completion_telemetry.patch

The two hunks are at:
  upstream/backend/open_webui/main.py:526   (import block extension)
  upstream/backend/open_webui/main.py:1840  (wrap inside process_chat)

